

	 
       urlLink The New York Times > Washington > Campaign 2004 > Report Finds Tax Cuts Heavily Favor the Wealthy : "The report calculated that households with incomes in that top 1 percent were receiving an average tax cut of $78,460 this year, while households in the middle 20 percent of earnings - averaging about $57,000 a year - were getting an average cut of only $1,090.  The new estimates confirm what independent tax analysts have long said: that Mr. Bush's tax cuts have been heavily skewed to the very wealthiest taxpayers."
    
